---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import ParallaxBanner from '../../components/ParallaxBanner.astro';
import ContactForm from '../../components/ContactForm.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Things to Do in Cibolo & Schertz, TX | Cody Posey Real Estate"
  description="Discover the best things to do in and around Cibolo and Schertz, Texas — from nature parks and wildlife safaris to live entertainment."
>
  <Navbar />
  <main style="padding-top: 80px;">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="cs-hero">
      <div class="cs-hero__overlay"></div>
      <div class="cs-hero__content">
        <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a> <span>/</span> <a href="/cibolo-schertz/">Cibolo / Schertz</a> <span>/</span> <span>Things to Do</span>
        </nav>
        <h1>Things to <span style="color:#FF1616;">Do</span></h1>
        <p>Outdoor adventures, family fun, and entertainment in and around the area</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Intro -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="cs-page-intro cs-page-intro--centered">The Cibolo/Schertz area offers more than just great neighborhoods. From 160-acre nature parks to wildlife safaris and live entertainment venues, there's plenty to do for families, outdoor enthusiasts, and everyone in between.</p>
        <div class="cs-expanded-content">
          <p>Cibolo and Schertz sit at the intersection of the Texas Hill Country and the greater San Antonio metro area, giving residents the best of both worlds. These neighboring cities have grown rapidly over the past two decades, attracting families and professionals who want access to big-city amenities while living in a community that still feels manageable and welcoming. Beyond the well-planned neighborhoods and top-rated schools, the area offers a surprising depth of recreational opportunities that keep residents active and engaged throughout the year.</p>
          <p>Crescent Bend Nature Park is one of the area's most valued outdoor spaces. Spanning 160 acres along Cibolo Creek, the park features paved and natural-surface trails for hiking, jogging, and mountain biking. The creek itself provides a scenic backdrop for morning walks and serves as a habitat for native wildlife including deer, hawks, and various reptile species. Covered picnic pavilions, open fields, and play areas make it a popular destination for family outings, and the park hosts community events including nature walks, trail runs, and outdoor fitness classes.</p>
          <p>Just a short drive from both cities, the Cibolo Nature Center and Farm offers over 100 acres of preserved Hill Country landscape. The center maintains several miles of trails through diverse ecosystems including grasslands, marshes, and old-growth cypress groves along Cibolo Creek. Educational programs for children and adults cover topics from native plant identification to wildlife conservation, and the working farm provides hands-on learning experiences. Volunteer opportunities are available year-round, giving residents a way to connect with the land and the community at the same time.</p>
          <h3>Family Attractions</h3>
          <p>The Natural Bridge Wildlife Ranch is one of the most popular family destinations in the region and sits just minutes from Cibolo and Schertz. This 500-acre drive-through safari park is home to over 500 animals from around the world, including giraffes, zebras, ostriches, and wildebeest. Visitors drive their own vehicles through the park while animals approach the car for feeding. Walking exhibits feature cheetahs, gibbons, and other species in naturalistic habitats. It is a memorable experience for children and adults alike and makes for an easy half-day outing from either city.</p>
          <p>Natural Bridge Caverns, located adjacent to the wildlife ranch, is another top family attraction. The largest commercial caverns in Texas descend 180 feet underground, revealing massive stalactite and stalagmite formations on guided tours. Above ground, the adventure village offers zip lines, a challenge course, gem mining, and a maze. Together, the caverns and wildlife ranch make this corner of the area one of the most family-friendly zones in the Hill Country region.</p>
          <h3>Entertainment and Nightlife</h3>
          <p>Retama Park brings a unique entertainment option to the Schertz area. The horse racing and events venue hosts live races during scheduled meets, simulcast wagering year-round, and special community events including concerts and festivals. The venue has become a gathering spot for residents looking for something different on a weekend evening. Live entertainment venues in the surrounding area, including outdoor concert spaces, add variety to the nightlife scene without requiring a drive into San Antonio.</p>
          <h3>Seasonal Events and Community Activities</h3>
          <p>Both Cibolo and Schertz maintain active community event calendars throughout the year. The Schertz Jubilee is one of the largest annual celebrations, featuring live music, carnival rides, food vendors, a parade, and fireworks. Cibolo hosts its own community festivals including holiday celebrations, movie nights in the park, and seasonal markets. Youth sports leagues, swim teams, and running clubs provide structured activities for families, while community pools and splash pads offer relief during the hot Texas summers. The area's proximity to San Antonio means major sporting events, concerts, and cultural attractions at the AT&T Center, Alamodome, and River Walk are all within a 20 to 30 minute drive.</p>
          <h3>Outdoor Recreation Beyond the Parks</h3>
          <p>Cycling and running enthusiasts appreciate the area's growing network of trails and bike lanes connecting neighborhoods to parks and commercial areas. Several public golf courses are located within a short drive, and the area's flat-to-rolling terrain makes it popular for road cycling. Fishing is available at nearby lakes and along Cibolo Creek, while hunting leases on surrounding ranch land provide seasonal opportunities for deer, dove, and turkey. The combination of suburban convenience and outdoor access is a defining feature of life in Cibolo and Schertz.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Activities -->
    <section class="section" style="background: var(--light-gray);">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>What to <span class="accent">Experience</span></h2>
        </div>

        <div class="cs-activity__grid">
          <a href="https://schertz.com/318/Crescent-Bend-Nature-Park" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cs-activity">
            <div class="cs-activity__header">
              <h3>Crescent Bend Nature Park</h3>
              <span class="cs-activity__tag">Outdoor</span>
            </div>
            <p>A 160-acre nature park along Cibolo Creek with hiking and biking trails, picnic areas, and scenic creek access. A local favorite for morning runs, family walks, and getting outdoors without leaving the area.</p>
          </a>

          <a href="https://wildliferanchtexas.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cs-activity">
            <div class="cs-activity__header">
              <h3>Natural Bridge Wildlife Ranch</h3>
              <span class="cs-activity__tag">Family</span>
            </div>
            <p>A 500-acre drive-through safari park with over 500 animals from around the world. One of the most popular family attractions in the region — kids and adults love the up-close animal encounters and walking exhibits.</p>
          </a>

          <a href="https://www.retamapark.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cs-activity">
            <div class="cs-activity__header">
              <h3>Retama Park</h3>
              <span class="cs-activity__tag">Entertainment</span>
            </div>
            <p>A horse racing and entertainment venue that hosts live races, simulcast events, and community gatherings throughout the year. A unique local venue for a fun evening out.</p>
          </a>

          <a href="https://www.retamapark.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cs-activity">
            <div class="cs-activity__header">
              <h3>Ashley Furniture HomeStore Pavilion</h3>
              <span class="cs-activity__tag">Entertainment</span>
            </div>
            <p>An outdoor concert and events venue that brings live music and entertainment to the Schertz area. Check their calendar for upcoming shows and community events throughout the season.</p>
          </a>

          <a href="https://www.cibolo.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cs-activity">
            <div class="cs-activity__header">
              <h3>Cibolo Nature Center</h3>
              <span class="cs-activity__tag">Outdoor</span>
            </div>
            <p>Over 100 acres of preserved land with hiking trails, educational programs, and native wildlife. The nature center offers guided walks, volunteer opportunities, and a peaceful escape into the Texas landscape.</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="section" style="background: #000; color: #fff; text-align: center;">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Ready to Call This Area <span class="accent">Home</span>?</h2>
        <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); max-width: 600px; margin: 1rem auto 2rem;">Great activities and outdoor access are just part of what makes Cibolo and Schertz special. Let me help you find the right home so you can enjoy it all as a local.</p>
        <div class="cs-cta__buttons">
          <a href="https://cposeyrealestate.idxbroker.com/idx/search/advanced" class="btn btn-primary">Search Homes</a>
          <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-outline">Ask About the Area</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
  <ParallaxBanner image="/images/generated/cibolo-schertz-home.png" />

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="faq-section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Things to Do in Cibolo and Schertz</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>What outdoor activities are available in the Cibolo and Schertz area?</summary>
            <p>The Cibolo and Schertz area offers a variety of outdoor recreation options. Crescent Bend Nature Park provides 160 acres of hiking, biking, and jogging trails along Cibolo Creek. The Cibolo Nature Center and Farm features over 100 acres of preserved Hill Country landscape with trails through grasslands, marshes, and cypress groves. Cycling, fishing along Cibolo Creek, and youth sports leagues are popular among residents. The area's growing trail network connects neighborhoods to parks, and nearby golf courses and hunting leases add additional options for outdoor enthusiasts.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>What are the best family-friendly attractions near Cibolo and Schertz?</summary>
            <p>Two of the region's top family attractions are located just minutes from Cibolo and Schertz. Natural Bridge Wildlife Ranch is a 500-acre drive-through safari park with over 500 animals, where families can feed giraffes and zebras from their car. Natural Bridge Caverns offers guided underground tours of the largest commercial caverns in Texas, plus above-ground activities like zip lines, gem mining, and a maze. Crescent Bend Nature Park and community pools provide everyday outdoor fun, while ZDT's Amusement Park in nearby Seguin adds roller coasters, go-karts, and mini golf to the mix.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>What community events and seasonal festivals take place in Cibolo and Schertz?</summary>
            <p>Both cities maintain active event calendars throughout the year. The Schertz Jubilee is one of the biggest annual celebrations, featuring live music, carnival rides, a parade, food vendors, and fireworks. Cibolo hosts holiday celebrations, outdoor movie nights, and seasonal community markets. Youth sports leagues, swim teams, and running clubs provide year-round structured activities for families. The area's close proximity to San Antonio also gives residents easy access to major sporting events, concerts, and cultural attractions at venues like the AT&T Center and the River Walk.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What outdoor activities are available in the Cibolo and Schertz area?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "The Cibolo and Schertz area offers a variety of outdoor recreation options. Crescent Bend Nature Park provides 160 acres of hiking, biking, and jogging trails along Cibolo Creek. The Cibolo Nature Center and Farm features over 100 acres of preserved Hill Country landscape with trails through grasslands, marshes, and cypress groves. Cycling, fishing along Cibolo Creek, and youth sports leagues are popular among residents. The area's growing trail network connects neighborhoods to parks, and nearby golf courses and hunting leases add additional options for outdoor enthusiasts."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What are the best family-friendly attractions near Cibolo and Schertz?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Two of the region's top family attractions are located just minutes from Cibolo and Schertz. Natural Bridge Wildlife Ranch is a 500-acre drive-through safari park with over 500 animals, where families can feed giraffes and zebras from their car. Natural Bridge Caverns offers guided underground tours of the largest commercial caverns in Texas, plus above-ground activities like zip lines, gem mining, and a maze. Crescent Bend Nature Park and community pools provide everyday outdoor fun, while ZDT's Amusement Park in nearby Seguin adds roller coasters, go-karts, and mini golf to the mix."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What community events and seasonal festivals take place in Cibolo and Schertz?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Both cities maintain active event calendars throughout the year. The Schertz Jubilee is one of the biggest annual celebrations, featuring live music, carnival rides, a parade, food vendors, and fireworks. Cibolo hosts holiday celebrations, outdoor movie nights, and seasonal community markets. Youth sports leagues, swim teams, and running clubs provide year-round structured activities for families. The area's close proximity to San Antonio also gives residents easy access to major sporting events, concerts, and cultural attractions at venues like the AT&T Center and the River Walk."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
    </script>

  <ContactForm context="I'd like to learn more about living in Cibolo/Schertz..." />
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .cs-hero {
    position: relative;
    height: 280px;
    background: url('/images/generated/cibolo-schertz-home.png') center/cover no-repeat;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
    color: #fff;
  }

  .cs-hero__overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.55);
  }

  .cs-hero__content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .cs-hero__content h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .cs-hero__content p {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  .breadcrumb span {
    margin: 0 0.3rem;
  }

  .cs-page-intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .cs-page-intro--centered {
    text-align: center;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--black);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* Activity Grid */
  .cs-activity__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .cs-activity {
    background: #fff;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    display: block;
  }

  .cs-activity h3 {
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .cs-activity:hover h3 {
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  .cs-activity__header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .cs-activity__header h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .cs-activity__tag {
    display: inline-block;
    background: #FF1616;
    color: #fff;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }

  .cs-activity p {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* CTA */
  .cs-cta__buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .cs-expanded-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 2rem auto 0;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .cs-expanded-content p {
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .cs-expanded-content h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  /* FAQ */
  .faq-section { padding: 4rem 0; background: #f9f9f9; }
  .faq-section h2 { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .faq-list { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .faq-item { background: #fff; border: 1px solid #eee; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .faq-item summary { padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; font-size: 1rem; list-style: none; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
  .faq-item summary::after { content: '+'; font-size: 1.3rem; color: #FF1616; font-weight: 700; }
  .faq-item[open] summary::after { content: '\2212'; }
  .faq-item p { padding: 0 1.5rem 1.25rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.8; font-size: 0.95rem; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .cs-activity__grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .cs-activity__header {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }
  }
</style>
